org.matsim.core.utils.collections

Interface RouterPriorityQueue<E>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<E>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MinHeap<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BinaryMinHeap, PseudoRemovePriorityQueue, WrappedBinaryMinHeap

    public interface RouterPriorityQueue<E>
extends Iterable<E>
    An interface for classes that can be used as priority queue. It offers a decreaseKey(...) method, which can be used by routers to increase the priority of re-visited nodes. An object's priority is defined by an additional argument of the add method and not determined based on a Comparator as in other implementations. As a result, objects do not have to be wrapped into QueueEntry objects which also include the object's priority.
    Author:
    cdobler
